        <body>
            <div>
                <entry xml:id="L1d6c40c423e645afb330f0b4464eaf75" n="12542">
                    <form>
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገኒ</foreign>
                    </form>
                    <sense xml:lang="en" source="#traces" xml:id="Tmain">
                        <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote>gani</quote>
                        </cit>
                        <gramGrp>
                            <pos expand="nomen proprium">n. pr.</pos>
                        </gramGrp> (place name) <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኦእግዚእየ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ሢመተ፡ ብሕት፡ ወደደ፡
                            ወሥመተ፡ ንጉሠ፡ ገኒ፡ ኢየአክለኒ፡ ወስከኒ፡ ዲበ፡ እሉ፡ ሢመተ፡ ነጋሤ፡ ጐዛም።</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                            <quote>O my lord the king, the office of bǝḥǝt wåd(d)ädä and the office
                                of nǝguśä Gäni are not enough for me; add me the office of nägaśe
                                Gʷåzzam in addition to them</quote>
                        </cit>’ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Getatchew1991EpistleOfHumanityT"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 69 l. 14-16 (ed.)</citedRange>
                        </bibl>, <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Getatchew1991EpistleOfHumanityV"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 55 l. 28-31(tr.)</citedRange>
                        </bibl> (‘<bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Perruchon1893Zarayaeqob"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 14</citedRange>
                        </bibl>. If Gän(i), unlike Gʷåzzam, could be ruled from the palace, then it
                        must have beed the region where the palace was located (Däbrä Bǝrhan).’ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Getatchew1991EpistleOfHumanityV"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 55 n. 113</citedRange>
                        </bibl>) <nd/>
                    </sense>
                </entry>
